entries.title: U.S. officials say ISIS leader, 10 ISIS fighters killed in raid
entries.description: Two senior officials say a U.S. assault operation in Somalia killed a top ISIS leader along with 10 other ISIS fighters and reportedly left no civilians killed or wounded. NBC’s Courtney Kube has the latest details.

entries.title: Ancient Egyptian treasures unveiled after Giza tombs excavation
entries.description: Egypt presented statues and other artefacts unearthed during a year-long dig at the Saqarra Necropolis in Giza. The objects date back to the fifth and sixth dynasties of the Old Kingdom, a period roughly between 2500 B.C and 2100 B.C.

entries.title: U.S. military raid in northern Somalia kills a senior ISIS leader and 10 ISIS fighters
entries.description: On Wednesday night a U.S. military operation in northern Somalia killed a senior ISIS leader and 10 other ISIS fighters, according to two senior U.S. officials.

entries.title: Afghan malnutrition rates at record high, U.N. food agency says
entries.description: Malnutrition rates in Afghanistan are at record highs — with half the country enduring severe hunger year-round — a spokesman for the U.N.'s World Food Program said.

entries.title: 'I have Prussians in my attic': Surprise revelation leads to rare Battle of Waterloo discovery
entries.description: When the elderly man approached after Bernard Wilkin had given a speech on battlefield bones, it's safe to say that Wilkin was not expecting the man's opening gambit.

entries.title: Ukraine has been promised dozens of tanks to fight Russia. Now what?
entries.description: The U.S. and German decision to send tanks to Ukraine may not move it any closer to a decisive victory, military analysts have warned.

entries.title: Chinese engineer sentenced to 8 years in U.S. prison for spying
entries.description: A former Chicago graduate student in electrical engineering was sentenced Wednesday to eight years in prison for spying for the Chinese government.

entries.title: Israeli forces kill at least nine during West Bank raid
entries.description: Israeli forces killed at least nine Palestinians, including an elderly woman, and wounded several others during a daytime raid in the occupied West Bank, Palestinian health officials said. Israel says the operation was targeting members of the Palestinian Islamic Jihad, a militia group suspected of planning multiple attacks against Israelis.

entries.title: Ukrainians shelter in metro station as Russian missiles target Kyiv
entries.description: Russia launched a barrage of missiles towards Ukraine, forcing people in Kyiv to take shelter in underground metro stations. Kyiv's military administration said more than 15 missiles fired at the Ukrainian capital had been shot down but urged people to remain in shelters.

entries.title: Germany arrests 2nd suspect in Russia spying case
entries.description: German authorities said Thursday that they have arrested a second person in connection with a high-profile espionage case that embarrassed Germany’s foreign intelligence agency.

entries.title: Spanish police investigate church attack as possible terror act
entries.description: A machete-wielding man killed a sexton and injured a priest at two Catholic churches in southern Spain before being arrested, Spain’s interior ministry said. Spanish authorities did not identify the suspect but said they are investigating the attacks as a possible act of terrorism.

entries.title: 1 dead in Spanish church machete attacks, terror link probed
entries.description: A machete-wielding man killed a sexton and injured a priest at two Catholic churches in the city of Algeciras on Wednesday before being arrested, Spain’s interior ministry said.

entries.title: Djokovic’s father seen posing with fans carrying Russian flags
entries.description: Australian Open organizers have issued a reminder  about their policy on “inappropriate flags” after a video emerged showing Novak Djokovic’s father posing for pictures with fans holding Russian flags.

entries.title: Palestinians say Israeli troops kill 9 in West Bank raid
entries.description: Israeli forces killed at least nine Palestinians and wounded several others during a raid in a flashpoint area of the occupied West Bank on Thursday, Palestinian health officials said.

entries.title: China says Covid deaths and severe cases have fallen over 70% since peak
entries.description: China says severe Covid-19 cases are down 72% from a peak early this month, while daily Covid deaths in hospitals have dropped 79% from their peak.

entries.title: Opium production is surging in Myanmar under military rule, U.N. says
entries.description: The production of opium in Myanmar has flourished under military rule, the U.N. said Thursday, with the cultivation of poppies up by a third in the past year.

entries.title: War with Russia rages as Ukraine’s government confronts an old enemy: Corruption
entries.description: KHARKIV, Ukraine — A cellphone video shared widely on social media shows a woman jumping up and down as she unwraps a gift.

entries.title: North Korea locks down capital city over ‘respiratory illness’
entries.description: Authorities in the North Korean capital, Pyongyang, have ordered a five-day lockdown due to rising cases of an unspecified respiratory illness.

entries.title: Biden announces U.S. will send 31 tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: President Biden announced today that the U.S. will send 31 powerful Abrams tanks to Ukraine. NBC News’ Kristen Welker on how lawmakers are responding and what this could mean for the ongoing conflict.
